<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the olden days, the way stock and bond trad=
ing worked is that you and I would agree on a trade (over the phone, on the=
 floor of the stock exchange, etc.), and we=E2=80=99d each make a little no=
te of it on a scrap of paper, and at the end of the day our clerks would co=
llect the scraps of paper and figure out what we=E2=80=99d bought and sold,=
 and then the clerks would go down to the vault in the basement, and my cle=
rk would get out the bond certificates I sold to you, and your clerk would =
get out a wad of cash, and our clerks would walk across the streets of Manh=
attan, and my clerk would hand your clerk the bonds and your clerk would ha=
nd my clerk the cash, and then our trade would be settled. And this process=
 took days, and had some failure rate, because we and our clerks were only =
human and the vaults were big and poorly organized and our handwriting, on =
the scraps of paper, was not always legible.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2023, almost all of this has been rendered =
abstract and put on computers. The bonds are entries on a computer, the cas=
h is an entry on a computer, the scraps=C2=A0of paper are computers, the fl=
oor of the stock exchange is mostly a computer, the whole process, from sta=
rt to finish, occurs on computers and often doesn=E2=80=99t involve any hum=
an actions at all. (It still often takes days?)=C2=A0This, of course, conce=
ntrates a lot of risk in the computers: If the computer systems fail, then =
all the trades fail, global finance is plunged into chaos, etc. So people p=
ut a lot of thought and effort and money into making the computer systems v=
ery robust and secure.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, though, there=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>a ba=
ckup mechanism, which is that if the computers fail, we can probably find s=
omeone to go walk across the streets of Manhattan to deliver bonds and cash=
. Last week Industrial &amp; Commercial Bank of China Ltd.=E2=80=99s US sec=
urities unit was hit by a ransomware attack, =E2=80=9Crendering it unable t=
o clear swathes of US Treasury trades after entities responsible for settli=
ng the transactions swiftly disconnected from the stricken system.=E2=80=9D=
 And, so, down to the vaults. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33352147.257416/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb2=
1iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMTAvd29ybGQtcy1iaWdnZXN0LWJhbmstZ=
m9yY2VkLXRvLXRyYWRlLXZpYS11c2Itc3RpY2stYWZ0ZXItaGFjaz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTEzMjNf=
TU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGV=
ybT0yMzExMTMmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd1b23=
545" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">Katherine Doherty, Liz Capo McCormick, and Alex Harris reporte=
d</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That forced ICBC to send the required settleme=
nt details to those parties by a messenger carrying a thumb drive as the st=
ate-owned lender raced to limit the damage.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The workaround =E2=80=94 described by market p=
articipants =E2=80=94 followed the attack by suspected perpetrator Lockbit,=
 a prolific criminal gang with ties to Russia that has also been linked to =
hits on Boeing Co., ION Trading UK and the UK=E2=80=99s Royal Mail. The str=
ike caused immediate disruption as market-makers, brokerages and banks were=
 forced to reroute trades, with many uncertain when access would resume.</p=
>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fine, it=E2=80=99s thumb drives, not paper bon=
d certificates, but still. In some ways it is nice that the electronic glob=
al financial markets have clumsily evolved from older and more manual proce=
sses; there is still some ancient memory of how to do stuff manually.</p>
